top_reviews.title: Convenient Fiber!
top_reviews.review_text: Very quick and easy way to get a significant source of fiber! From my experience, don’t eat a whole serving at once the first time, or your intestines might let you know about it! Slowly incorporate it into your current cereal or add small amounts to yogurt or as an oatmeal topping. Then work your way up to a full serving! It would be great with some dried cranberries or golden raisins mixed in! One not-so-great aspect is that it quickly soaks up all of your milk, so wait until the very last minute to add your milk before digging in!

top_reviews.title: It reminds me of childhood, so I like it.
top_reviews.review_text: I first tried this cereal when I was an extremely young child, my mother gave me a small bag of it dry to keep me occupied while she worked on speaking to someone. My only memory that accompanies that is that I loved the texture and flavor, it was just a satisfying snack. After that I had completely forgotten about it, until one day I had a random craving. Now I hadn't thought about this cereal for so long, it turned out I completely about this cereal, but I craved the nostalgia of that memory, the satisfying crunch, and the familiar flavor. After a few months, I thought I was going crazy as I couldn't remember the what the darn thing even looked like. Eventually after a few rounds of cereal roulette, I had found this box. I was a bit disheartened to find that the taste had changed a bit, but that may be more the fault of my aging tongue rather than the formula or really anything in General Mills part. I eat this cereal in the morning best paired with 2% milk, as to not heavily out weigh milk to cereal flavor. Then I usually put a small amount in sandwich bag to take with me to work. The look of this cereal allows me to eat these as a snack without really being judged, since it doesn't look like typical cereal. This cereal is one of my favorites, if not my absolute favorite for bringing me a moment of the past back into my day to day trudge.

top_reviews.title: No More BHT!
top_reviews.review_text:
Thank you GM for removing BHT from the cereal! For anyone not paying attention, BHT has been in most cereals, snacks, and foods most American's have been feeding our kids. It's been banned in Europe and other countries. Thankfully in the past few months, it's been removed and my kids can finally enjoy cereal from time to time again.
They also improved their packaging and I was happy to easily open the plastic bag without it ripping down the side.

top_reviews.title: Childless adult tested & approved as well
top_reviews.review_text: I am an adult 29 year old woman and I 10/10 recommend Kix. I personally like to “spice it up” with fresh fruit and oat milk but I’m sure there are millions of ways to eat this. It also is oil free- which as a person who doesn’t eat most oils, I’ve often thought of it as a cheese-less Cheeto like dry snack. I will continue buying this cereal, even if it has Paw Patrol characters on the box.
